%20point%20for%20the%20pouches%20was%2C%20though%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fwellness%2F2023%2F11%2F07%2Fapplesauce-recalls-lead-exposure-testing%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20cinnamon%20as%20a%20possible%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELead%20poisoning%20of%20any%20volume%20can%20be%20extremely%20dangerous%20for%20anyone%2C%20but%20even%20more%20so%20for%20young%20children%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnceh%2Flead%2Fprevention%2Fhealth-effects.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECenters%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20child%20is%20exposed%20to%20lead%20by%20touching%2C%20swallowing%2C%20or%20breathing%20it%20in%2C%20it%20can%20have%20severe%20impacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20low%20levels%20of%20lead%20in%20blood%20have%20been%20shown%20to%20negatively%20affect%20a%20child's%20intelligence%2C%20ability%20to%20pay%20attention%2C%20and%20academic%20achievement%2C%26quot%3B%20reads%20the%20agency's%20site.%20%26quot%3BThe%20effects%20of%20lead%20poisoning%20may%20be%20permanent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20isn't%20a%20%26quot%3Bsafe%26quot%3B%20amount%20of%20lead%20exposure%2C%20the%20CDC%20considers%20anything%20over%20a%20blood%20lead%20level%20of%203.5%20micrograms%20per%20deciliter%20to%20be%20higher%20than%20normal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChildren%20reported%20to%20the%20FDA%20were%20found%20to%20have%20blood%20lead%20levels%20from%204%20to%2029%20micrograms%20per%20deciliter%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FHealth%2FwireStory%2Fchildren-sickened-fruit-pouches-tainted-lead-fda-105110506%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20ABC%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FDA%20is%20recommending%20any%20child%20who%20may%20have%20consumed%20the%20impacted%20products%20be%20screened%20for%20lead%20poisoning%2C%20which%20can%20be%20done%20thr