th%20Hertfordshire%20Museum%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20now%20refer%20to%20emperor%20Elagabalus%20with%20female%20pronouns%20of%20she%20and%20her%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fentertainment-arts-67484645%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBBC%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ereported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20museum%20said%20the%20decision%20was%20prompted%20by%20classical%20texts%20that%20allege%20the%20emperor%20once%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BCall%20me%20not%20Lord%2C%20for%20I%20am%20a%20Lady.%26quot%3B%20The%20words%20were%20written%20by%20Cassius%20Dio%2C%20a%20well-known%20Roman%20historian%20and%20administrator.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20museum%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bonly%20polite%20and%20respectful%20to%20be%20sensitive%20to%20identifying%20pronouns%20for%20people%20in%20the%20past%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20museum%20owns%20a%20silver%20denarius%20minted%20in%20the%20reign%20of%20Elagabalus%2C%20who%20ruled%20Rome%20from%20218AD%20until%20his%20assassination%2C%20aged%2018%2C%20in%20222AD%2C%20and%20the%20coin%20has%20been%20used%20in%20LGBT-themed%20displays%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraph.co.uk%2Fnews%2F2023%2F11%2F20%2Ftrans-roman-emperor-hitchin-museum-claim-pronouns-woke%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETelegraph%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ereported.%20In%20displays%20featuring%20the%20coin%2C%20information%20about%20it%20and%20Elagabalus%2C%20the%20ruler%20will%20be%20referred%20to%20as%20she.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElagabalus%20became%20a%20controversial%20figure%20over%20his%20short%20reign%2C%20developing%20a%20reputation%20for%20sexual%20promiscuity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20married%20five%20times-%20four%20times%20to%20women%2C%20and%20once%20to%20Hiercoles%2C%20a%20former%20slave%20and%20chariot%20driver.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECassius%20Dio%2C%20a%20senator%20and%20contemporary%20of%20Elagabalus%2C%20writes%20in%20his%20historical%20chronicles%20mentioned%20that%20the%20emperor%20%26q