20office%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20gazette%20notification%20issued%20by%20the%20law%20ministry%20on%20Thursday%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bombay%20high%20court%20collegium%20recommended%20to%20the%20SC%20collegium%20on%20October%204%2C%202021%20that%20Sundaresan%20%E2%80%93%20a%20lawyer%20specialised%20in%20commercial%20law%20%E2%80%93%20should%20be%20appointed%20as%20a%20judge.%20On%20February%2016%2C%202022%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20collegium%20sent%20his%20name%20to%20the%20Union%20government.%20Nine%20months%20later%2C%20in%20November%202022%2C%20the%20government%20asked%20the%20SC%20collegium%20to%20reconsider%20the%20recommendation%20because%20of%20views%20that%20Sundaresan%20had%20expressed%20on%20social%20media%20on%20several%20matters%20that%20will%20be%20considered%20by%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SC%20collegium%20in%20January%20this%20year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fpdf%2FCollegium%2F19012023_105747.pdf%5C%22%3Ereiterated%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20decision%20to%20appoint%20Sundaresan%20as%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court.%C2%A0It%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cviews%20on%20social%20media%20attributed%20to%20the%20candidate%2C%20do%20not%20furnish%20any%20foundation%20to%20infer%20that%20he%20is%20biased%E2%80%9D.%20The%20issues%20on%20which%20opinions%20have%20been%20attributed%20to%20the%20candidate%20are%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20and%20have%20been%20extensively%20deliberated%20upon%20in%20the%20print%20and%20electronic%20media%2C%20the%20collegium%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-things-we-learnt-when-the-sc-collegium-finally-became-transparent%5C%22%3EThe%20Things%20We%20Learnt%20When%20the%20SC%20Collegium%20Finally%20Became%20%E2%80%98Transparent%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20collegium%20said%20that%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20Sundaresan%20expressed%20his%20views%20does%20not%20justify%20the%20inference%20that%20he%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Chighly%20biased%20opinionated%20person%E2%80%9D%20or%20that%20he%20has%20been%20%E2%80%9Cselectively%20critical%20on%20the%20social%20media%20on%20the%20important%20policies%2C%20initiatives%20and%20directions%20of%20the%20Government%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20judges%20noted.%20There%20is%20also%20no%20material%20to%20indicate%20that%20the%20expressions%20used%20by%20Sundaresan%20are%20%E2%80%9Csuggestive%20of%20his%20links%20with%20any%20political%20party%20with%20strong%20ideological%20leanings%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20citizens%20have%20the%20right%20to%20free%20speech%20and%20expression%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Expression%20of%20views%20by%20a%20candidate%20does%20not%20disentitle%20him%20to%20hold%20a%20constitutional%20office%20so%20long%20as%20the%20person%20proposed%20for%20judgeship%20is%20a%20person%20of%20competence%2C%20merit%20and%20integrity%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20collegium%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20judge%2C%20Sundaresan%E2%80%99s%20expertise%20in%20commercial%20law%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20be%20an%20asset%20to%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%2C%20which%20has%20a%20large%20volume%20of%20cases%20of%20commercial%20and%20securities%20laws%2C%20among%20other%20branches%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20collegium%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP-led%20Union%20government%20has%20sought%20more%20influence%20on%20the%20appointment%20of%20judges.%20After%20the%20top%20court%20struck%20down%20a%20law%20that%20would%20have%20given%20the%20power%20of%20appointing%20and%20transferring%20judicial%20officers%20to%20the%20executive%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20adopted%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-collegium-judges-appointment-centre-pick-and-choose%5C%22%3Epick-and-choose%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20policy%20to%20thwart%20collegium%20recommendations.%20While%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20repeatedly%20warned%20against%20such%20actions%2C%20the%20trend%20has%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20earlier%20this%20week%2C%20the%20top%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-union-govt-failure-clear-appointment-two-sikh-lawyers%5C%22%3Ewarned%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20government%20of%20%E2%80%9Cembarrassing%20outcomes%E2%80%9D%20if%20such%20a%20policy%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700743852000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F23181243%2FScreenshot-2023-11-23-at-6.11.51%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2F18-months-collegium-somasekhar-sundaresan-appointed-bombay-hc-judge%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Union%20government%20had%20in%20November%202022%20asked%20the%20SC%20collegium%20to%20reconsider%20the%20recommendation%20because%20of%20views%20that%20Sundaresan%20expressed%20on%20social%20media.%20The%20collegium%20rejected%20the%20objection.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2F18-months-collegium-somasekhar-sundaresan-appointed-bombay-hc-judge%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pakistan%20ex-PM%20Imran%20Khan's%20party%20directed%20to%20hold%20leadership%20poll%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700743838000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105449801%2Cimgsize-1599055.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fpakistan-ex-pm-imran-khans-party-directed-to-hold-leadership-poll%2Farticleshow%2F105449757.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105449757.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fpakistan-ex-pm-imran-khans-party